24/12/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- The Pristina regional court ordered 30-day detentions Friday (December 22nd) for three people arrested in connection with a huge weapons bust last week in the town of Drenica.
The Kosovo Police Service has identified one of the detainees as Naim Bazaj, political adviser to Kosovo Minister of Labour Ibrahim Selmani.
In other news Friday, Serbian police announced the arrest of 15 customs officials, suspected of being part of a smuggling network that caused some 5m euros worth of damage to the state budget.
(Tanjug, RTS, Vecer, Danas - 23/12/06;
Koha Ditore - 22/12/06)
